<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Diagnoses with NAAT(PCR) <i>or</i> culture</li>
<li>We add doxycycline in case of co-infection with Chlamydia</li>
<li><b>Clinical features</b> :
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Purulent urethral discharge (yellow-green)</li>
<li>PID <i>Pelvic inflammatory disease</i></li>
<li><b>Fitz-Hugh-Curtis syndrome</b> :</li>
<li>Can lead to salpingitis -&gt; infertility in 20% cases
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Liver capsule inflammation, commonly as complication of pelvic inflammatory disease in females</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li><i>Lipooligosaccharide does not have long O antigen chains</i></li>
</ul>
