<div id="outline-container-orgfb84f22" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgfb84f22">43.Vibrionaceae- V. Cholerae, other Vibrio species associated with human diseases</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgfb84f22">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><i>Vibrios are among the most common bacteria in surface waters worldwide</i></li>
<li><b>Curved/Comma shaped aerobic rods, possessing a polar flagellum(motile)</b></li>
<li>Vibrios grow at a very high pH(8.5-9.5) and are rapidly killed by acid(acid labile)</li>
</ul>
</div>
